<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="432" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,585,755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,585,611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, N. L." box="[276,419,585,611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="1 - 252" refId="ref2965" refString="Bruce, N. L. (2009) The marine fauna of New Zealand: Isopoda, Aegidae (Crustacea). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir, 122, 1 - 252." type="journal article" year="2009">Bruce (2009</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 7) showed that the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1850" box="[697,790,585,611]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aegidae</taxonomicName>
is basally divided into two major clades, one containing 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1815" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[151,357,620,647]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Aega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,209,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Aega</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[217,357,620,647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="306 - 400" refId="ref3187" refString="Leach, W. E. (1815) A tabular view of the external characters of four classes of animals which Linne arranged under Insecta with the distribution of the genera composing three of these classes into Orders, and description of several new genera and species. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 11, 306 - 400. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1813. tb 00065. x" type="journal article" year="1815">Leach, 1815</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bovallius, 1885" authorityName="Bovallius" authorityYear="1885" box="[372,675,620,647]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Aegiochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[372,489,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Aegiochus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bovallius, C." box="[496,675,620,647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref2821" refString="Bovallius, C. (1885) A new isopod from the Swedish Arctic Expedition of 1883. Bihang til Kongeliga Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar, 10, 1 - 12, pls. 1, 2." type="book chapter" year="1885">Bovallius, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bruce, 2009" authorityName="Bruce" authorityYear="2009" box="[732,1011,621,647]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Aegapheles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,861,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Aegapheles</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, N. L." box="[870,1011,621,647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="1 - 252" refId="ref2965" refString="Bruce, N. L. (2009) The marine fauna of New Zealand: Isopoda, Aegidae (Crustacea). NIWA Biodiversity Memoir, 122, 1 - 252." type="journal article" year="2009">Bruce, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the other containing 
<taxonomicName authority="Milne Edwards, 1840" authorityName="Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1840" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1361,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Alitropus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Milne Edwards, H." pageId="1" pageNumber="432" refId="ref3308" refString="Milne Edwards, H. (1840) Histoire Naturelle des Crustaces Comprenent l'anatomie, la physiologie et la classification de ces animaux. Roret, Paris, ii + 638 pp." type="book" year="1840">Milne Edwards, 1840</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1818" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[334,582,657,683]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Rocinela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,434,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Rocinela</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[440,582,657,683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="338 - 354" refId="ref3269" refString="Leach, W. E. (1818) Cymothoadees. In: Cuvier, F. (Ed.), Dictionnaire des Sciences Naturelles. Strasbourg et Levrault, Paris, pp. 338 - 354." type="book chapter" year="1818">Leach, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Harger, 1880" authorityName="Harger" authorityYear="1880" box="[593,848,657,683]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Syscenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,694,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Syscenus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harger, O." box="[701,848,657,683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="297 - 462" refId="ref3137" refString="Harger, O. (1880) Report on the marine Isopoda of New England and adjacent waters. Report of the U. S. Commission for Fisheries, 6, 297 - 462. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 1391" type="journal article" year="1880">Harger, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tattersall, 1909" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1909" box="[903,1206,657,683]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Xenuraega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,1026,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Xenuraega</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tattersall, W. M." box="[1032,1206,657,683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="210 - 219" refId="ref3341" refString="Tattersall, W. M. (1909) II. Amphipoda and Isopoda, with descriptions of two new species. Memoirs of the Challenger Society, 1, 210 - 219." type="journal article" year="1909">Tattersall, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In that analysis 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1909" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Xenuraega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Xenuraega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sister taxon to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harger" authorityYear="1880" box="[474,575,693,719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Syscenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[474,575,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Syscenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and these two genera are sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[957,1057,693,719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Rocinela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1057,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Rocinela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both genera lack a frontal lamina and have an elongate pleon that has all pleonites with free lateral margins, none being posteriorly directed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
